    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Center Support Disassembly</title>
        <table id="t07010157">
            <title>Special Tools</title>
            <tgroup cols="2">
                <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.94*"/>
                <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.06*"/>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <graphic filename="../figST1/ST1190A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="112px"
                                     scalefitheight="112px"/>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Compressor, Clutch Spring</para>
                            <para>ZTSE9121</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <graphic filename="../figST2/ST2719A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="112px"
                                     scalefitheight="112px"/>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Alignment Cone</para>
                            <para>ZTSE9144</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Note the location of the seal ring ends and how they overlap for correct assembly.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard the direct clutch seal rings.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010325" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0066478.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the No. 6 thrust washer.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010326" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0057659.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using the special tool, remove the intermediate piston return spring snap ring.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010327" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0018757.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the intermediate piston return spring.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010328" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0057661.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard the intermediate piston.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010329" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0057662.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the new intermediate piston.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010330" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0018758.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Inspect the intermediate piston inner and outer seals.</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Inspect the check ball for free movement.</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If the sealing surface or the bushing show signs of damage or wear, a new center support must be
                    installed.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the center support for damage or wear.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010331" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0018759.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Inspect the center support bushing.</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Inspect the center support sealing surface.</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>&#8226; Verify that the air bleed orifice located on the center support is in the 12:00 o'clock position
            and is not clogged. Apply 138 kPa (20 psi) air pressure from the piston side of the center support to verify
            that the bleed orifice is clear.
        </para>
    </svcsubproc>
